        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:49PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Usta, or 18 miles north of Faith, moving east at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Perkins County to the northeast of Usta and southeast of Meadow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
